context: While true exhibition matches are not uncommon, most matches tell <a0_0>a story analogous to a scene in a play or film, or an episode of a serial drama:<a0_0/> The face will sometimes win (<a2_0>triumph<a2_0/>) or sometimes lose (<a1_0>tragedy<a1_0/>). Longer story arcs can result from multiple matches over the course of time. Since most promotions have a championship title, competition for the championship is a common impetus for stories. Also, anything <a3_0>from a character's own hair to their job with the promotion<a3_0/> can be wagered in a match. The same type of good vs. evil storylines were also once popular in roller derby.
